==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*''(UK):'' [[aeroplane]]
*''(diminutive):'' [[plane]]''

===Etymology===
From Greek ''[[ἀήρ]]'', through Latin ''[[aero-]]'', combining form for '''air''' + plane, from Latin ''[[planum]]'', '''flat'''.

===Noun===
'''airplane'''  (''plural:'' '''[[airplanes]]''')
# A powered [[aircraft]] with fixed [[wing]]s used for [[transportation]] of humans and goods; for [[amusement]] or [[entertainment]]; and in [[warfare]].

